response: "{ \"title\": \"Easy: Prime Number Checker\", \"description\": \"Write a function `is_prime` that takes an integer `n` as input and returns `True` if it's a prime number, `False` otherwise.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef is_prime(n: int) -> bool:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `n` (int): A positive integer.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns `True` if the input integer is a prime number, `False` otherwise.\\n\", \"code\": \"def is_prime(n: int) -> bool:\\n    if n <= 1:\\n        return False\\n    for i in range(2, int(n ** 0.5) + 1):\\n        if n % i == 0:\\n            return False\\n    return True\", \"tests\": [\"assert is_prime(7) == True\", \"assert is_prime(10) == False\", \"assert is_prime(23) == True\", \"assert is_prime(48) == False\"] }"
